Jerry -

Just my opinion, but the only advantage I see with a blog is that you don't
need to know any of the code necessary to build a website, you can just choose
a template and get going.  I've got two podcasts and created websites for each
of them.  I'm a Webmaster, so writing the code was considerably easier than
dealing with the limitations of a template, so place that into the mix.  I
wrote a series of administrative programs that makes it very easy for me to
place information onto the websites.

And I think that that is really the most important thing - make it easy for
yourself.  If you shudder when thinking about the work required to maintain a
website, then a blog template would probably be the easiest way to go.  You
really don't want this end of things to become a chore for you - your energy is
better devoted to creating a great podcast that people want to listen to.

Cheers -

george

