If your intention is to have different content on the blog that is a great
idea. So many podcasters do not have a blog that is relevant to the topic of
their podcast, and I think they are missing out on a great opportunity to
enhance their listeners experience, while getting more listeners in the
process. I think if you combine the 2, it might confuse people, and make
podcast posts harder to find, since they usually come out less frequently
than text posts. The more great content you have to offer, the more
potential readers/listeners you can attract. Not to mention that search
engines will like your site better if you have consistent and relevant
content.

To me their 3 types of people. Those who prefer audio, those who prefer
text, or those who prefer both. I prefer text, because it is easier to get
the information quickly. I listen to podcasts when I have the time. My
favorite podcast, Slice of Scifi, has a site that is updated constantly with
relevant news regarding the genre the podcast is based on, so I subscribe to
both feeds.

Another of my favorites, DIY Endeavours, is hosted by Matt Selznick, and he
has a blog as well. I subscribe to both as well.

Remember, that if you want to grab your audience to both sites, the content
must be able to coexist with each other, or you risk alienating them. Don't
have a blog about tinker toys, and them tell them to listen to your podcast
about Swedish meatball making.

Also, having a podcast on Wordpress is one of the best things you could do.
Do you use the Podpress plugin?

