Wordpress and Blogger are both blogging platforms.  Both provide
content via dated posts, both will let people leave comments to
interact with you, etc.  The major differences from a podcast
perspective are that Wordpress offers more podcast-friendly features
(including the Podpress plugin) and is installed on your own site,
while Blogger is simpler and you have to use their site.

It really is redundant to have both.  There's nothing Blogger can do
that Wordpress can't.

